#
# Now we do the randomization of variables, and other computations
# as needed for this problem.  Sometimes we compute the answers here.
#
$AC = random(2,10);
$alpha=random(20,70,5);  #angle in degrees
$r=$alpha*3.14159265/180;  #angle in radians

#find the answers
$AB=$AC*cos($r);
$BC=$AC*sin($r);
$beta=90-$alpha;


BEGIN_TEXT
Refer to the right triangle in the figure. Click on the picture to see it more clearly.
$BR
\{ image("right_triangle.gif") \}
$BR
If , \( AC=$AC \) and the angle \( \alpha=$alpha ^\circ \), find any missing angles or 
sides. Give your answer to at least 3 decimal digits.

	$PAR
$BR	AB  = \{ans_rule(20)\}
$BR     BC  = \{ans_rule(20)\}
$BR    \( \beta \)= \{ans_rule(20)\}
        
END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($AB));
ANS(num_cmp($BC));
ANS(num_cmp($beta));

